column1:
^{a} Coding: 1 = yes; 0 = no.
^{b} Province: 1 = west; 0 = east.
^{c} Results for age of onset and number of cigarettes a day are reported for
the effects of 5 units increase, i.e. 5 years for age onset smoking and 5
cigarette.
^{d} Educational level: 1 = medium or high, 0 = low; age is in years.
^{e} One-tailed p-value, since the cluster variance cannot be negative.
